National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Head of the Office of the President of Ukraine Andriy Yermak in Istanbul. Sullivan expressed unwavering support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, stating that the United States and its allies will not be deterred by Russia's violations of international law. He also mentioned that severe consequences will be imposed on anyone who supports Russia's alleged annexation. The two officials discussed the situation at Ukraine's Zaporizhzhya Nuclear Power Plant and Ukraine's efforts to export food through the United Nations. Sullivan reiterated the United States' commitment to assisting Ukraine, including the recently signed $12 billion in additional aid by President Biden.